model
Class Invitation

java.lang.Object
  model.Invitation

public class Invitation
extends java.lang.Object

Author:
Eric Foote The Invitation class represents an event that can be created by a user. Each Invitation has a name and a description, which are visible to all users and are set when the invitation is created. The Invitation class also stores a list of the phone numnbers of each invited user, and a list of options for users to vote on. When all invited users have voted, or some set timeout has passed, the Invitation is moved to "active" state, and users can no longer vote. An invitation may also have one or more categories for users to vote on. An example of a category might be a time or place that the users need to decide on; each category can then have one or more options that users can choose from.
